<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<GameData>
	<Language_en_US>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_CSVASSAL">
			<Text>City-State Liberation</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_CSVASSAL_HELP">
			<Text>You have liberated the city-state and they are indebted to you. What do you suppose we do with them?</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_CSVASSAL_CHOICE_1">
			<Text>We should install a government that favors us...</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_CSVASSAL_CHOICE_2">
			<Text>We should open up the city-state toward the world...</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_CSVASSAL_CHOICE_3">
			<Text>Leave their people alone. They should be independent in their thinking and actions even if they oppose us in the near future.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_CSVASSAL_CHOICE_1_HELP">
			<Text>[ICON_BULLET][ICON_CITY_STATE] City-State becomes [COLOR_TECH_TEXT]Allied[ENDCOLOR] toward your causes. A Sphere of Influence is installed in the City-State's Government forcing them to align in your favors and become their permanent ally![NEWLINE][ICON_BULLET]Rebels will create a movement that will attempt to topple down your aligned-government until international forces arrive to stop it![NEWLINE][NEWLINE][COLOR_NEGATIVE_TEXT]If the World Congress has not been founded, there is no one to recognize this action! This will do nothing![ENDCOLOR]</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_CSVASSAL_CHOICE_2_HELP">
			<Text>[ICON_BULLET][ICON_CITY_STATE] City-State becomes [COLOR_TECH_TEXT]Friendly[ENDCOLOR]. An Open Door Policy is issued to the City-State and no one is able to become their ally![NEWLINE][NEWLINE][COLOR_NEGATIVE_TEXT]If the World Congress has not been founded, there is no one to recognize this policy![ENDCOLOR]</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_CSVASSAL_CHOICE_3_HELP">
			<Text>[ICON_BULLET][ICON_CITY_STATE] City-State becomes [COLOR_TECH_TEXT]Independent[ENDCOLOR].</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_CSVASSAL2">
			<Text>City-State Forgiveness</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_CSVASSAL2_HELP">
			<Text>Their soon-to-be former governor approach you and begs for forgiveness. What do you suppose we do with them?</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_CSVASSAL2_CHOICE_1">
			<Text>Yes, they are misguided by the ways of their once governship. Let them rule with some self-independence once more!</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_CSVASSAL2_CHOICE_2">
			<Text>No, install a puppet government and replace this governor with someone toward us.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_CSVASSAL2_CHOICE_1_HELP">
			<Text>You liberate the puppet state and grant the state autonomy.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_CSVASSAL2_CHOICE_2_HELP">
			<Text>Ignore their complaints and the puppet state adds to your empire.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_CSVASSAL2_CHOICE_1_NOTIFY_SHORT">
			<Text>War Changes Hands!</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_CSVASSAL2_CHOICE_1_NOTIFY">
			<Text>Recently, a city-state has fallen to a foreign force! However, the forces were forgiving and granted them self-autonomy once again!</Text>
		</Row>
	</Language_en_US>
